<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="609" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="609">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="609">
The status of 
<taxonomicName family="Combretaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. exilis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" rank="species" species="exilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="609">C. exilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been surrounded by uncertainty for over 40 years. It has been considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith &amp; Cognato" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Smith &amp; Cognato" baseAuthorityYear="2021" family="Combretaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. pseudotenuis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" rank="species" species="pseudotenuis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="609">C. pseudotenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wood, SL" journalOrPublisher="Great Basin Naturalist Memoirs" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" pagination="1 - 1359" refId="B88" refString="Wood, SL, 1982. The bark and ambrosia beetles of North and Central America (Coleoptera: Scolytidae), a taxonomic monograph. Great Basin Naturalist Memoirs 8: 1 - 1359" title="The bark and ambrosia beetles of North and Central America (Coleoptera: Scolytidae), a taxonomic monograph." volume="8" year="1982">Wood 1982</bibRefCitation>
) and a 
<normalizedToken originalValue="‘probable’">'probable'</normalizedToken>
synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith &amp; Cognato" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Smith &amp; Cognato" baseAuthorityYear="2021" family="Combretaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. pseudotenuis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" rank="species" species="pseudotenuis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="609">C. pseudotenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.17203" author="Wood, SL" journalOrPublisher="Great Basin Naturalist" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" pagination="347 - 365" refId="B86" refString="Wood, SL, 1976. New synonymy and new species of American bark beetles (Coleoptera: Scolytidae) Part III. Great Basin Naturalist 36: 347 - 365, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.17203" title="New synonymy and new species of American bark beetles (Coleoptera: Scolytidae) Part III." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.17203" volume="36" year="1976">Wood 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wood, SL" journalOrPublisher="The Great Basin Naturalist Memoirs" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" pagination="1 - 1553" refId="B92" refString="Wood, SL, Bright, DE, 1992. A catalog of Scolytidae and Platypodidae (Coleoptera), part 2: Taxonomic index. The Great Basin Naturalist Memoirs 13: 1 - 1553" title="A catalog of Scolytidae and Platypodidae (Coleoptera), part 2: Taxonomic index." volume="13" year="1992">Wood and Bright 1992</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Wood, SL" journalOrPublisher="Brigham Young University, M. L. Bean Life Science Museum; Provo" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" refId="B91" refString="Wood, SL, 2007. Bark and ambrosia beetles of South America (Coleoptera: Scolytidae). Brigham Young University, M.L. Bean Life Science Museum; Provo" title="Bark and ambrosia beetles of South America (Coleoptera: Scolytidae)." year="2007">Wood (2007)</bibRefCitation>
later treated the species as valid and 
<bibRefCitation author="Bright, DE" journalOrPublisher="Occasional Papers of the Florida State Collection of Arthropods" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" pagination="1 - 491" refId="B11" refString="Bright, DE, 2019. A taxonomic monograph of the bark and ambrosia beetles of the West Indies (Coleoptera: Curculionoidea: Scolytidae). Studies on West Indian Scolytidae (Coleoptera) 7. Occasional Papers of the Florida State Collection of Arthropods 12: 1 - 491" title="A taxonomic monograph of the bark and ambrosia beetles of the West Indies (Coleoptera: Curculionoidea: Scolytidae). Studies on West Indian Scolytidae (Coleoptera) 7." volume="12" year="2019">Bright (2019)</bibRefCitation>
returned this species to 
<taxonomicName class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xyleborus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xyleborus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="609">Xyleborus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without discussion. This species belongs in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hopkins" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Malvaceae" genus="Coptoborus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Coptoborus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="609">Coptoborus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it shares the characters outlined in the generic diagnosis.
</paragraph>
